# PROJECT SUMMARY

Project Title: Scientific Calculator Using Java Swing

University: Khushal Khan Khattak University, Karak (KKKUK)

Instructor: Dr. Arshad Iqbal

# Developed By:

Naeem Ullah

Abdul Salam

Muhammad Afshan


Introduction:
This project is a Scientific Calculator application developed using Java Swing. The main purpose of this project is to design and implement a user-friendly desktop calculator capable of performing both basic and advanced mathematical operations.

# Purpose of the Project:
The purpose of this project is to enhance practical knowledge of Java programming, GUI development, and event handling. It also helps in understanding object-oriented programming concepts and mathematical logic implementation.

# Scope of the Project:
The calculator can be used by students, teachers, and professionals for performing daily mathematical and scientific calculations efficiently.

# Key Features:

Basic arithmetic operations

Scientific functions (sin, cos, tan, log, square root, power)

Interactive graphical interface

Error handling

Fast and accurate calculations

Tools and Technologies:

Java

Java Swing

AWT

Event Handling

# Conclusion:
The Scientific Calculator project is a practical implementation of Java Swing GUI concepts. It improves programming skills and demonstrates how desktop applications are built using Java.
